# Expect a non-zero exit: recursion deeper than MYON_MAX_CALL_DEPTH must be
# caught by the interpreter's call-depth guard and reported as a runtime error
# (graceful exit code 1), rather than overflowing the C stack and dying with
# SIGSEGV (exit code 139).  Only the non-zero exit is pinned, not the exact
# message text (same convention as step12_overflow.err).
